Duit is Digital Mars D programing language OO wrapper for Gtk+.
Duit is release on th LGPL license.

Here you can find the development version of Duit.
Duit is to replace DUI.

Duit is as stable as the old DUI and much more complete.
Duit is a work in progress.

Requirements:
-------------
- linux or windows(2000, XP)
- Gtk libs
- dmd installation
  (on your home directory on linux or the root directory on windows)
optionally:
- openGL libs (mesa is fine on linux)
- gtkglext

installation:
-------------
only the development version of Duit is supplied for now.
the installation depends on the setup of your development environment.
consider leds (http://www.dsource.org/projects/leds/browser/downloads/)
for your D development projects.
This means that to release your project you must include the Duit lib
on your deliverable or statically link to Duit - please pay attention
to the license.

compile the lib and the test programs:
--------------------------------------
to compile Duit Duitgl and the tests execute

$ makeAll.sh on linux 
$ makeAll.bat on windows

then run the tests
$ DuitTests - tests the wrapping for Gtk+
$ SimpleGL - simple test for openGL extension
$ ShapesGL - test for openGL extension
